The paper focuses on deep embedding learning for object recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a multi-task learning framework and a quadruplet-based loss function suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of the method to fine-grained datasets suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
